<title>Maria Axenovich</title>
<p></p>
<p>
<url href="https://www.math.kit.edu/iag6/~axenovich/en">Dr. Maria Axenovich</url> works in graph theory and combinatorics. One of the main topics of her research is unavoidable structures in graphs and their partitions. Dr. Axenovich was born in Novosibirsk, Russia, where she did her undergraduate studies. </p>
<p>After completing my Ph.D. in the University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign, USA, under the guidance of Zoltan Furedi, and having long-term research visits in the Mathematics Institute in Oxford, UK, and the Renyi Mathematics Institute in Budapest, Hungary, Dr. Axenovich was a professor at Iowa State University, Ames, IA, USA. Currently, Dr. Axenovich is a professor at the Karlsruhe Institute of Technology, Karlsruhe, Germany.
</p>
