<p>
Dr. Butler's primary mathematical interests are spectral graph theory, enumerative combinatorics, mathematics of juggling, discrete geometry, and generally mathematics of fun things.  Among other things, he can do eight perfect faro shuffles in a row, and is willing to teach this to anyone who stops by his office.
